title: In court, Maduro pleads not guilty, says he's 'still president' of Venezuela
subhed: Thousands of people marched through Caracas in support of Maduro as his former deputy, Delcy Rodriguez, was sworn in on Monday as interim president. Donald Trump has said he wants to work with Rodriguez and the rest of Maduro's former team, provided that they submit to US demands on oil.

US recommends fewer childhood vaccines in major shift
subhed: At the end of 2024, the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) recommended 17 pediatric immunizations for all individuals, the agency said. Now that number is 11. President Donald Trump praised the changes, commenting that MAHA (Make America Healthy Again) moms 'have been praying for these common sense reforms for many years.'

title: Denmark warns US against taking Greenland by force
subhed: PM Jens-Frederik Nielsen said that "everything would stop" if the US were to employ military force against another NATO country.

title: Paris court finds 10 guilty of cyber-harassing Brigitte Macron
subhed: One person was jailed and eight were given suspended prison sentences for posting 'numerous malicious comments' falsely claiming that President Emmanuel Macron's wife was born a man.
byline: Le Monde with AP and AFP

title: Phil Gunson: If Trump does not force Venezuela to hold free elections, 'they can agree on almost everything'
subhed: The Caracas-based International Crisis Group analyst Phil Gunson underlines in an interview that Donald Trump has had 'harsh words' for opposition figure Maria Corina Machado and sees the possibility of an agreement between the US administration and the Venezuelan regime's remaining leaders.

For Putin, US operation in Venezuela is a double-edged sword
subhed: The capture of President Nicolas Maduro by the US weakens Ukraine's allies, who have positioned themselves as defenders of democracy and international law. It also deals a blow to Moscow, depriving it of a key partner and threatening its oil revenues.

title: Maduro capture marks new blow to dying international order
subhed: Venezuela's allies condemned an 'illegal act of aggression' while countries aligned with the US urged restraint but sought to avoid directly criticizing Donald Trump.

title: 'Trump is torn between the UAE and Saudi Arabia'
subhed: US President Donald Trump faces pressure from Mohammed bin Salman to oppose the separatist strategy pursued by the United Arab Emirates in Sudan, and even more so in Yemen, writes columnist Jean-Pierre Filiu, a professor at Sciences Po Paris.
